parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
the engine turns off suddenly
the ignition switch fails to return to the "on" position
the key fob gets stuck in the ignition
the vehicle fails to start
and warning lights illuminate on the instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ignition switch fails to return to the "on" position
the key fob gets stuck in the ignition
and the vehicle fails to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle goes into limp mode
the transmission gets stuck in 2nd gear
and the vehicle loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sunroof drain can cause water to pour into the vehicle, leading to electrical damage, water damage, and mold/mildew buildup.
symptoms: Water pours into the vehicle through the sunroof
causing electrical damage
water damage
and mold/mildew buildup.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Smoke comes out of the hood
and the wire connected to the alternator is shorting and sparking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the ignition cylinder can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
the vehicle loses power

the headlights dim or turn off
the instrument panel gauges flash or malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle shifts into neutral unexpectedly

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transfer case failure can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle shifts into neutral unexpectedly

the "Service 4WD" message appears on the dashboard

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Four-wheel drive system failure can cause the vehicle to lose traction or control, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to start

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage or failure.
